 supplementary knowledge base document. Let me first search for some key information to ensure accuracy: Using Tool | Think Based on the video transcript, I need to create: 1. ✅ The main HTML SOP document (already created) 2. A separate n8n workflow JSON file that can be imported 3. A knowledge base document to track all resources Key workflow components identified from video: - Schedule Trigger (runs daily at midnight) - Google Sheets (Get Rows with filter for \"for production\" status) - AI Agent (Gemini Flash with structured output for movie trailer scenes) - Split Out node (break scenes into individual items) - HTTP Request - Generate Videos (Piapi.ai text-to-video) - HTTP Request - Get Videos (check video status) - Aggregate (consolidate video results) - Switch (route by status: completed/pending/error) - Wait node (for pending videos - 5 seconds) - Google Sheets Update (error logging) - HTTP Request - Create Movie (JSON2Video) - HTTP Request - Get Movie Status (polling) - If node (check if done) - Wait node (false branch - 5 seconds loop) - HTTP Request - Download Video - Google Drive Upload - Google Sheets Update (success logging) The workflow needs: - Google Sheets with columns: ID, Idea, Caption, Channel Style Prompt, Character Style Prompt, Production Status, Final Output, Publishing Status, Error Log - API keys: Piapi.ai, JSON2Video, Google (Sheets + Drive), Gemini - JSON2Video template with 6 scenes (video + text elements) I should create a realistic n8n workflow JSON structure that users can import. While I can't test it, I can create a template structure based on standard n8n JSON format. Now let me create a comprehensive knowledge base document and a detailed implementation guide: Using Tool | Markdown Generation Generate content before line 1, instruction: Create a comprehensive Knowledge Base document in Markdown format for \"AI Movie Generation Automation - Knowledge Base & Resources\" Structure: # AI Movie Generation Automation - Knowledge Base ## Document Control - Version: 1.0 - Last Updated: 2025-10-24 - Document Purpose: Central repository for all resources, links, and reference materials ## 📚 Quick Reference Links ### Official Documentation List all official documentation links for: - n8n documentation - Piapi.ai API docs - JSON2Video API docs - Google Sheets API - Google Drive API - Gemini AI documentation ### Video Tutorial - Original video link - Timestamp breakdown of key sections ## 🔑 API Keys & Credentials Checklist Create a table with: - Service Name - API Key Location - Required Permissions - Cost per Request - Monthly Free Tier - Documentation Link ## 📊 Google Sheets Structure ### Required Columns (with data types and examples) Detail each column: 1. ID (number) 2. Idea (text) 3. Caption (text) 4. Channel Style Prompt (text) 5. Character Style Prompt (text) 6. Production Status (dropdown values) 7. Final Output (URL) 8. Publishing Status (dropdown values) 9. Error Log (text) ### Sample Data Rows Provide 3 example rows with realistic movie ideas ### Status Workflow Explain the status progression: - Empty → For Production → Processing → Done/Error ## 🎬 JSON2Video Template Structure ### Template Configuration - Template ID: [USER_SPECIFIC] - Number of Scenes: 6 - Resolution: 1080p - Aspect Ratio: 16:9 ### Scene Structure Detail each scene's configuration with: - Video element settings - Text element settings (font, size, position) - Transition effects - Duration ### Dynamic Variables Mapping Show the mapping between n8n outputs and template placeholders ## 💰 Cost Analysis ### Per Video Cost Breakdown - Piapi.ai: $X per video - JSON2Video: $X per render - Google Cloud: $X per operation - Gemini AI: $X per request - Total per video: $X ### Monthly Projections Table showing: - Videos/Day: 1, 5, 10, 30 - Monthly Cost - Revenue at $X/video - Profit Margin ## 🚀 Monetization Strategies ### 1. Direct Video Sales - Pricing tiers - Target markets - Sales channels ### 2. SaaS Model - Subscription tiers - Feature differentiation - Customer acquisition cost ### 3. White Label Solution - Licensing model - Implementation services - Support packages ### 4. Agency Services - Package pricing - Client onboarding - Delivery timeline ### 5. Educational Content - Course creation - Workshop pricing - Affiliate opportunities ## 🎯 Conversion Optimization ### Landing Page Elements - Hero section copy - Social proof elements - Demo video placement - CTA strategy ### Email Sequence - Welcome email - Onboarding sequence (5 emails) - Upgrade triggers - Re-engagement campaign ### Pricing Psychology - Anchor pricing - Value ladder - Scarcity tactics - Guarantee strategy ## 🐛 Common Errors Database Create a comprehensive table: - Error Code/Message - Root Cause - Solution Steps - Prevention Method - Related Resources Include at least 15 common errors from: - API authentication - Rate limiting - Data format issues - Timeout errors - Missing credentials ## 🔧 Advanced Customizations ### Workflow Variations 1. Multi-language support 2. Different video styles 3. Bulk processing mode 4. Priority queue system ### Integration Options - Zapier connections - Webhook triggers - Airtable alternative - Notion database sync ### AI Model Alternatives - OpenAI vs Gemini comparison - Leonardo AI integration - Runway ML options - Stability AI possibilities ## 📈 Performance Benchmarks ### Speed Metrics - Average generation time: X minutes - Bottleneck analysis - Optimization tips ### Quality Metrics - Video resolution - Scene consistency - Caption accuracy - Character consistency ## 🎓 Training Resources ### For Team Members - Onboarding checklist - Video tutorials (create list) - Common mistakes - Best practices ### For Clients - Getting started guide - FAQ document - Support ticket system - Community forum ## 📅 Maintenance Schedule ### Daily Tasks - Monitor error logs - Check API credits - Review generated videos ### Weekly Tasks - Cost analysis - Performance review - Template updates ### Monthly Tasks - API key rotation - Backup verification - Security audit ## 🔐 Security & Compliance ### Data Protection - API key management - Environment variables - Backup strategy ### Terms of Service - AI usage policies - Content ownership - Copyright considerations ## 🌐 Community & Support ### Official Communities - n8n Discord/Forum - AI automation groups - Video production forums ### Expert Contacts - n8n consultants - AI integration specialists - Video production experts ## 📋 Changelog Track all changes to: - Workflow versions - SOP updates - New features added - Bug fixes ## 🎯 Success Metrics & KPIs Define and track: - Videos generated/day - Success rate % - Average cost per video - Customer satisfaction score - Revenue per customer - Churn rate - Support ticket volume ## 🔄 Update Process How to update: - Workflow modifications - Template changes - Documentation revisions - Knowledge base additions Format with proper Markdown syntax, tables where appropriate, and clear hierarchies. Perfect! Now let me create a separate document with the n8n workflow JSON template and detailed configuration instructions: Using Tool | Markdown Generation Generate content before line 1, instruction: Create a detailed n8n Workflow Configuration Guide in Markdown format. # n8n Workflow JSON & Configuration Guide ## 📦 Workflow Import Instructions ### Step 1: Access n8n 1. Open your n8n instance (cloud or self-hosted) 2. Navigate to Workflows section 3. Click \"Add Workflow\" or use the + button ### Step 2: Import Method Choose one of two methods: **Method A: JSON Import** 1. Click the three-dot menu (⋯) in the top right 2. Select \"Import from File\" or \"Import from URL\" 3. Paste the JSON provided below 4. Click \"Import\" **Method B: Manual Creation** Follow the node-by-node setup guide in Section 3 ## 🔧 Complete n8n Workflow Structure ### Workflow Overview - **Name:** AI Movie Generator - Automated - **Description:** Generates complete short films from story ideas using AI agents - **Trigger Type:** Schedule (Cron) - **Estimated Runtime:** 5-10 minutes per movie - **Total Nodes:** 18 ### Node Configuration Map Create a detailed table with ALL nodes: | Node # | Node Type | Node Name | Purpose | Dependencies | Configuration Priority | |--------|-----------|-----------|---------|--------------|----------------------| | 1 | Schedule Trigger | Daily Trigger | Start workflow at midnight | None | HIGH | | 2 | Google Sheets | Get Topic Rows | Fetch production-ready topics | Node 1 | HIGH | | 3 | AI Agent | Generate Movie Scenes | Create storyboard with Gemini | Node 2 | HIGH | | 4 | Split Out | Split Scenes | Break into individual scenes | Node 3 | MEDIUM | | 5 | HTTP Request | Generate Videos | Send to Piapi.ai for generation | Node 4 | HIGH | | 6 | HTTP Request | Get Video Status | Retrieve completed videos | Node 5 | HIGH | | 7 | Aggregate | Consolidate Videos | Merge all video results | Node 6 | MEDIUM | | 8 | Switch | Status Router | Route by completion status | Node 7 | HIGH | | 9 | Wait | Pending Wait | 5-second delay for processing | Node 8 (pending) | LOW | | 10 | Google Sheets | Log Errors | Write errors to sheet | Node 8 (error) | MEDIUM | | 11 | HTTP Request | Create Movie Trailer | Send to JSON2Video | Node 8 (complete) | HIGH | | 12 | HTTP Request | Get Movie Status | Check rendering status | Node 11 | HIGH | | 13 | If | Check Completion | Verify if movie is done | Node 12 | MEDIUM | | 14 | Wait | Render Wait | 5-second polling delay | Node 13 (false) | LOW | | 15 | HTTP Request | Download Video | Fetch final video file | Node 13 (true) | HIGH | | 16 | Google Drive | Upload to Drive | Store completed video | Node 15 | MEDIUM | | 17 | Google Sheets | Update Success Log | Mark as complete | Node 16 | MEDIUM | ## 📝 Detailed Node Configurations ### Node 1: Schedule Trigger ```json { \"name\": \"Schedule Trigger\", \"type\": \"n8n-nodes-base.scheduleTrigger\", \"typeVersion\": 1, \"position\": [250, 300], \"parameters\": { \"rule\": { \"interval\": [ { \"field\": \"days\", \"daysInterval\": 1 } ] }, \"triggerTimes\": { \"item\": [ { \"hour\": 0, \"minute\": 0 } ] } } } ``` **Configuration Steps:** 1. Click \"Add node\" → \"Trigger\" → \"Schedule\" 2. Set \"Trigger Interval\" to \"Days\" 3. Set \"Days Between Triggers\" to 1 4. Set \"Trigger at Hour\" to 0 (midnight) 5. Set \"Trigger at Minute\" to 0 6. Click \"Execute Node\" to test **Expected Output:** - Triggers at 00:00:00 daily - No data output (trigger only) --- ### Node 2: Google Sheets - Get Topic Rows ```json { \"name\": \"Get Topic Rows\", \"type\": \"n8n-nodes-base.googleSheets\", \"typeVersion\": 4, \"position\": [450, 300], \"parameters\": { \"operation\": \"read\", \"sheetId\": \"YOUR_SHEET_ID\", \"range\": \"Sheet1\", \"options\": { \"filter\": { \"conditions\": [ { \"column\": \"Production Status\", \"condition\": \"equals\", \"value\": \"For Production\" } ] }, \"returnFirstMatch\": true } }, \"credentials\": { \"googleSheetsOAuth2Api\": { \"id\": \"YOUR_CREDENTIAL_ID\", \"name\": \"Google Sheets Account\" } } } ``` **Configuration Steps:** 1. Click \"Add node\" → \"Regular\" → \"Google Sheets\" 2. Click \"Credentials\" → \"Create New\" 3. Follow Google OAuth2 authentication flow 4. Set \"Operation\" to \"Read\" 5. Select your Google Sheet document 6. Select \"Sheet1\" (or your sheet name) 7. Toggle \"Filter\" ON 8. Set filter: Column = \"Production Status\", Condition = \"equals\", Value = \"For Production\" 9. Toggle \"Return Only First Match\" ON 10. Test the connection **Expected Input:** - Trigger activation **Expected Output:** ```json { \"ID\": 1, \"Idea\": \"A hero's journey through a cyberpunk city\", \"Caption\": \"In a neon-lit future, one person stands against the system\", \"Channel Style Prompt\": \"Cinematic, dark, cyberpunk aesthetic\", \"Character Style Prompt\": \"Lone warrior, tech-enhanced, mysterious\", \"Production Status\": \"For Production\", \"Final Output\": \"\", \"Publishing Status\": \"\", \"Error Log\": \"\" } ``` --- ### Node 3: AI Agent - Generate Movie Scenes ```json { \"name\": \"Generate Movie Scenes\", \"type\": \"@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.agent\", \"typeVersion\": 1, \"position\": [650, 300], \"parameters\": { \"promptType\": \"define\", \"text\": \"Generate a movie trailer with 6 scenes for this idea: {{$json.Idea}}\\n\\nStyle: {{$json['Channel Style Prompt']}}\\nCharacter: {{$json['Character Style Prompt']}}\\nCaption: {{$json.Caption}}\\n\\nCreate exactly 6 scenes with:\\n- Scene number\\n- Visual description (detailed prompt for video generation)\\n- Caption text\\n- Duration in seconds (3-5 seconds each)\", \"hasOutputParser\": true, \"options\": { \"systemMessage\": \"You are a professional film director and screenwriter. Create compelling, visually rich trailer scenes that tell a story. Each scene should be cinematic, emotionally engaging, and technically detailed for AI video generation. Always output exactly 6 scenes in valid JSON format.\" } } } ``` Add sub-nodes: - **Chat Model:** Google Gemini Flash - **Output Parser:** Structured Output Parser with JSON schema **JSON Schema for Output Parser:** ```json { \"type\": \"object\", \"properties\": { \"scenes\": { \"type\": \"array\", \"items\": { \"type\": \"object\", \"properties\": { \"scene_number\": {\"type\": \"number\"}, \"visual_prompt\": {\"type\": \"string\"}, \"caption\": {\"type\": \"string\"}, \"duration\": {\"type\": \"number\"} }, \"required\": [\"scene_number\", \"visual_prompt\", \"caption\", \"duration\"] } } } } ``` **Configuration Steps:** 1. Add AI Agent node 2. Set \"Prompt Type\" to \"Define Below\" 3. Paste user message with field mappings 4. Add System Message 5. Connect Chat Model → Add \"Google Gemini\" 6. Configure Gemini credentials 7. Add Output Parser → \"Structured Output Parser\" 8. Paste JSON schema 9. Toggle \"Require Specific Output Format\" ON 10. Execute and verify 6 scenes generated **Expected Output:** ```json { \"scenes\": [ { \"scene_number\": 1, \"visual_prompt\": \"Wide shot of a neon-lit cyberpunk city at night, rain pouring down, holographic advertisements flickering, dark and moody atmosphere\", \"caption\": \"In a world consumed by technology...\", \"duration\": 4 }, { \"scene_number\": 2, \"visual_prompt\": \"Close-up of a lone figure in a dark hood, face partially obscured, cybernetic eye glowing blue, rain dripping off hood\", \"caption\": \"One person dares to resist\", \"duration\": 3 } // ... 4 more scenes ] } ``` --- ### Node 4: Split Out - Split Scenes **Configuration Steps:** 1. Add \"Split Out\" node 2. Set \"Field to Split Out\" to: `output.scenes` (use expression editor) 3. Full expression: `{{$json.output.scenes}}` 4. Leave other settings at default **Expected Input:** - Array of 6 scenes from AI Agent **Expected Output:** - 6 separate items, each containing one scene --- ### Node 5: HTTP Request - Generate Videos (Piapi.ai) **Configuration:** ```json { \"name\": \"Generate Videos\", \"type\": \"n8n-nodes-base.httpRequest\", \"typeVersion\": 4, \"position\": [1050, 300], \"parameters\": { \"method\": \"POST\", \"url\": \"https://api.piapi.ai/api/v1/video/text-to-video\", \"authentication\": \"genericCredentialType\", \"genericAuthType\": \"httpHeaderAuth\", \"sendHeaders\": true, \"headerParameters\": { \"parameters\": [ { \"name\": \"X-API-Key\", \"value\": \"={{$credentials.piapiApiKey}}\" } ] }, \"sendBody\": true, \"bodyParameters\": { \"parameters\": [ { \"name\": \"prompt\", \"value\": \"={{$json.visual_prompt}}\" }, { \"name\": \"duration\", \"value\": \"={{$json.duration}}\" } ] }, \"options\": { \"batching\": { \"batch\": { \"batchSize\": 1, \"batchInterval\": 10000 } } } } } ``` **Configuration Steps:** 1. Add HTTP Request node 2. Set Method to \"POST\" 3. URL: `https://api.piapi.ai/api/v1/video/text-to-video` 4. Authentication → Generic Credential Type → HTTP Header Auth 5. Header Name: `X-API-Key` 6. Header Value: Your Piapi.ai API key 7. Send Body → JSON 8. Body Parameters: - prompt: `{{$json.visual_prompt}}` - duration: `{{$json.duration}}` 9. Options → Batching: - Batch Size: 1 - Batch Interval: 10000ms (10 seconds) 10. Pin the output data after execution **Expected Output:** ```json { \"task_id\": \"vid_abc123def456\", \"status\": \"processing\", \"created_at\": \"2025-10-24T10:30:00Z\" } ``` --- ### Node 6: HTTP Request - Get Video Status **Configuration:** 1. Duplicate Node 5 (Generate Videos) 2. Change Method to \"GET\" 3. Update URL to: `https://api.piapi.ai/api/v1/video/status/{{$json.task_id}}` 4. Toggle \"Send Body\" OFF 5. Remove batching options 6. Rename to \"Get Video Status\" **Expected Output:** ```json { \"task_id\": \"vid_abc123def456\", \"status\": \"completed\", \"video_url\": \"https://cdn.piapi.ai/videos/vid_abc123def456.mp4\", \"duration\": 4.2, \"resolution\": \"1080p\" } ``` --- ### Node 7: Aggregate - Consolidate Videos **Configuration:** 1. Add \"Aggregate\" node 2. Set \"Mode\" to \"Combine All Items\" 3. Field: Leave default (aggregates all) **Purpose:** Combines all 6 individual video results into one data structure --- ### Node 8: Switch - Status Router **Configuration:** 1. Add \"Switch\" node 2. Create 3 routing rules: **Route 1 - Completed:** - Output: \"Completed\" - Condition: `{{$json.status}}` equals `completed` **Route 2 - Pending:** - Output: \"Pending\" - Condition: `{{$json.status}}` equals `processing` **Route 3 - Error:** - Output: \"Error\" - Condition: `{{$json.error}}` is not empty --- ### Nodes 9-17: Continue with similar detailed configurations... ## 🔐 Credentials Setup ### Google Sheets OAuth2 1. Go to Google Cloud Console 2. Create new project or select existing 3. Enable Google Sheets API 4. Create OAuth 2.0 credentials 5. Add authorized redirect URI: `https://your-n8n-instance.com/rest/oauth2-credential/callback` 6. Copy Client ID and Client Secret 7. In n8n: Credentials → Add → Google Sheets OAuth2 8. Paste credentials and authenticate ### Piapi.ai API Key 1. Sign up at piapi.ai 2. Navigate to Dashboard → API Keys 3. Generate new API key 4. Copy the key 5. In n8n: Credentials → Add → Header Auth 6. Name: `X-API-Key` 7. Value: Your Piapi.ai key ### JSON2Video API Key (Similar process) ### Google Drive OAuth2 (Similar to Google Sheets) ## ✅ Pre-Flight Checklist Before executing the workflow: - [ ] All API keys configured and tested - [ ] Google Sheet created with correct column structure - [ ] At least one row marked \"For Production\" - [ ] JSON2Video template created with 6 scenes - [ ] Template ID updated in workflow - [ ] Google Drive folder created - [ ] Folder ID updated in workflow - [ ] All nodes connected properly - [ ] Each node tested individually - [ ] Credentials have required permissions - [ ] API billing enabled (if required) - [ ] Sufficient API credits available ## 🚀 First Execution Steps 1. **Test Individual Nodes First** - Execute Schedule Trigger (manual test) - Execute Get Topic Rows (verify data fetched) - Execute AI Agent (verify 6 scenes generated) - Continue testing each node in sequence 2. **Fix Any Errors** - Check error messages - Verify field mappings - Confirm API responses match expected format 3. **Run Complete Workflow** - Click \"Execute Workflow\" button - Monitor execution in real-time - Check for any node failures - Review final output in Google Drive 4. **Verify Results** - Open Google Sheet - Check \"Production Status\" updated to \"Done\" - Verify \"Final Output\" has video URL - Play the video to confirm quality - Check Google Drive for uploaded file ## 📊 Monitoring & Maintenance ### Daily Checks - Review Error Log column in Google Sheets - Check API usage/credits - Verify scheduled executions running ### Weekly Tasks - Analyze video quality trends - Review cost per video - Update prompts for better results - Clear completed rows from sheet ### Monthly Tasks - Rotate API keys (security best practice) - Backup workflow JSON - Review and optimize bottlenecks - Update documentation with lessons learned ## 🐛 Troubleshooting Quick Reference | Symptom | Likely Cause | Solution | |---------|--------------|----------| | Schedule not triggering | Timezone mismatch | Check n8n server timezone settings | | No rows returned | Filter condition wrong | Verify \"Production Status\" exact spelling | | AI Agent fails | Invalid prompt | Check field mappings use correct syntax | | Video generation timeout | API overloaded | Increase batching interval to 15000ms | | JSON2Video fails | Template ID wrong | Copy correct template ID from JSON2Video dashboard | | Google Drive upload fails | Permission issue | Re-authenticate Google Drive credentials | | Infinite pending loop | Status check incorrect | Verify status field mapping: `{{$json.status}}` | ## 📦 Backup & Export ### Export Workflow 1. Click workflow menu (⋯) 2. Select \"Download\" 3. Save JSON file with date: `ai-movie-workflow-2025-10-24.json` 4. Store in secure location ### Version Control - Save workflow after each modification - Use descriptive version names - Keep changelog of major changes ## 🎓 Next Steps After successful setup: 1. Generate your first test movie 2. Review output quality 3. Adjust prompts for better results 4. Scale to multiple movies 5. Implement monetization strategy 6. Build client acquisition system --- **Document Version:** 1.0 **Last Updated:** 2025-10-24 **Maintained By:** [Your Name] **Support Contact:** [Your Email] Excellent! Now let me create one more critical document - a Quick Start Implementation Checklist that's action-oriented and easy to follow: Using Tool | Markdown Generation Generate content before line 1, instruction: Create a Quick Start Implementation Guide in Markdown - an action-oriented, step-by-step checklist format. # 🚀 AI Movie Generation - Quick Start Implementation Guide ## ⏱️ Total Setup Time: 2-3 Hours This guide will take you from zero to your first AI-generated movie in a single session. --- ## Phase 1: Account Setup (30 minutes) ### ✅ Step 1.1: n8n Platform Setup (10 min) **Choose Your Option:** **Option A: n8n Cloud (Recommended for beginners)** - [ ] Go to https://n8n.io/cloud - [ ] Click \"Start Free Trial\" - [ ] Sign up with email - [ ] Verify email address - [ ] Complete profile setup - [ ] Note your instance URL: `https://[your-name].app.n8n.cloud` **Option B: Self-Hosted n8n** - [ ] Have Docker installed on your system - [ ] Run: `docker run -it --rm --name n8n -p 5678:5678 n8nio/n8n` - [ ] Access at: `http://localhost:5678` - [ ] Create admin account - [ ] Configure environment variables **✓ Success Criteria:** You can log into n8n dashboard --- ### ✅ Step 1.2: Google Account Configuration (10 min) **Google Cloud Console:** - [ ] Go to https://console.cloud.google.com - [ ] Create new project: \"AI-Movie-Generator\" - [ ] Note Project ID: ___________________ **Enable APIs:** - [ ] Search for \"Google Sheets API\" → Enable - [ ] Search for \"Google Drive API\" → Enable **Create OAuth Credentials:** - [ ] APIs & Services → Credentials - [ ] Create Credentials → OAuth 2.0 Client ID - [ ] Application type: Web application - [ ] Name: \"n8n Integration\" - [ ] Authorized redirect URIs: `https://[your-n8n-url]/rest/oauth2-credential/callback` - [ ] Click Create - [ ] **Copy Client ID:** ___________________ - [ ] **Copy Client Secret:** ___________________ **✓ Success Criteria:** You have Client ID and Secret copied --- ### ✅ Step 1.3: Piapi.ai Account (5 min) - [ ] Go to https://piapi.ai - [ ] Sign up for account - [ ] Navigate to Dashboard - [ ] Go to API Keys section - [ ] Generate new API key - [ ] **Copy API Key:** ___________________ - [ ] Add credits to account (minimum $10 recommended) - [ ] Current balance: $___________ **✓ Success Criteria:** API key copied and account funded --- ### ✅ Step 1.4: JSON2Video Account (5 min) - [ ] Go to https://json2video.com - [ ] Sign up for account - [ ] Navigate to Dashboard → API - [ ] Generate API key - [ ] **Copy API Key:** ___________________ - [ ] Check free tier: _____ renders/month - [ ] Add credits if needed **✓ Success Criteria:** API key copied --- ### ✅ Step 1.5: Google Gemini API (Optional - 5 min) - [ ] Go to https://makersuite.google.com/app/apikey - [ ] Create API key - [ ] **Copy API Key:** ___________________ - [ ] Or use OpenAI as alternative **✓ Success Criteria:** AI API key obtained --- ## Phase 2: Google Sheets Database Setup (15 minutes) ### ✅ Step 2.1: Create Master Spreadsheet (5 min) - [ ] Open Google Sheets - [ ] Create new spreadsheet - [ ] Name it: \"AI Movie Production Database\" - [ ] **Copy Sheet URL:** ___________________ - [ ] Extract Sheet ID from URL (between /d/ and /edit) - [ ] **Sheet ID:** ___________________ --- ### ✅ Step 2.2: Configure Column Headers (3 min) **Row 1 - Create these exact column headers:** - [ ] Column A: `ID` - [ ] Column B: `Idea` - [ ] Column C: `Caption` - [ ] Column D: `Channel Style Prompt` - [ ] Column E: `Character Style Prompt` - [ ] Column F: `Production Status` - [ ] Column G: `Final Output` - [ ] Column H: `Publishing Status` - [ ] Column I: `Error Log` **Format Headers:** - [ ] Make Row 1 bold - [ ] Fill with light gray background - [ ] Freeze Row 1 (View → Freeze → 1 row) --- ### ✅ Step 2.3: Add Sample Data Rows (7 min) **Row 2 - Example 1:** ``` ID: 1 Idea: A cyberpunk warrior's last stand against an AI overlord in a neon-lit city Caption: In the heart of darkness, one spark of humanity remains Channel Style Prompt: Cinematic, dark cyberpunk, neon colors, rainy night, blade runner aesthetic, 4K quality Character Style Prompt: Lone warrior, cybernetic enhancements, mysterious hooded figure, glowing blue eyes Production Status: For Production Final Output: [leave empty] Publishing Status: [leave empty] Error Log: [leave empty] ``` **Row 3 - Example 2:** ``` ID: 2 Idea: A deep sea explorer discovers an ancient underwater civilization Caption: 20,000 leagues beneath, secrets of the deep awaken Channel Style Prompt: Underwater cinematography, bioluminescent creatures, mysterious ancient ruins, blue-green color palette Character Style Prompt: Deep sea explorer in advanced diving suit, sense of wonder and discovery Production Status: For Production Final Output: [leave empty] Publishing Status: [leave empty] Error Log: [leave empty] ``` **Row 4 - Example 3:** ``` ID: 3 Idea: Time traveler witnesses the birth and death of the universe in 60 seconds Caption: From the Big Bang to the final star—witness eternity Channel Style Prompt: Cosmic, space documentary style, time-lapse of galaxies, epic scale, vibrant nebulas Charact"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"[Content truncated — view full chat at source URL]"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"Source: "},{"type":"link","href":"https://www.genspark.ai/agents?id=940d44e4-55f0-452d-81dd-1bd75dd77227","children":[{"text":"https://www.genspark.ai/agents?id=940d44e4-55f0-452d-81dd-1bd75dd77227"}]}]}]
